    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "71b68cf7-530b-465b-aae9-783fd148996c",
      "text": "The second part of the principle deals with how members are compensated for funds invested in a Co-operative, and how surpluses should be used. Unlike for-profit [[corporations]], co-operatives are a form of [[social enterprise]]. Given this, there are at least three purposes for which surplus funds can be used, or distributed, by a Co-operative."
