      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e1b0b73a-845d-4a19-9248-767403972e89",
      "text": "* “Members usually receive limited compensation, if any, on capital subscribed as a condition of membership.”\n* “Developing their co-operative, possibly by setting up reserves, part of which at least would be indivisible;” in other words, the surplus can be reinvested in the co-operative.\n* \"Benefiting members in proportion to their transactions with the co-operative;” for example, a [[Consumers' Co-operative]] may decide to pay [[dividend]]s based on purchases (or a 'divvi').\n* “Supporting other activities approved by the membership.”"
